!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

shallow /ˈʃæləʊ/

(shallower,shallowest) 

1. ADJ A shallow container, hole, or area of water measures only a short distance from the top to the bottom. 浅的 

例： Put the milk in a shallow dish. 把牛奶倒进一个浅盘里。 

2. ADJ If you describe a person, piece of work, or idea as shallow , you disapprove of them because they do not show or involve any serious or careful thought. (人、作品、主意等) 浅薄的 [表不满] 

例： I think he is shallow, vain and untrustworthy. 我认为他浅薄、虚荣、不可信。 

3. ADJ If your breathing is shallow , you take only a very small amount of air into your lungs at each breath. (呼吸) 浅的 

例： She began to hear her own taut, shallow breathing. 她开始听到自己紧张、短促的呼吸。

</div>

